g.title: COMMENT_8fadc00+1
g.text: !> brief Send and receive the major MPI packages
!> details For each mesh, NM, controlled by MPI process, SNODE, send data to other meshes, NOM.

g.title: COMMENT_9145000+1
g.text: Start the communications. Note that MPI_STARTALL starts the persistent send/receives

g.title: COMMENT_8fc1240+1
g.text: Set up sends for one-time exchanges or persistent send/receives.

g.title: COMMENT_8fbce80+1
g.text: Determine the maximum number of radiation angles that are to be sent

g.title: COMMENT_8ff2280+1
g.text: Exchange the number of solid surface cells whose back side is in another mesh

g.title: COMMENT_8fc7080+1
g.text: Allocate 1-D arrays to hold major mesh variables that are to be sent to neighboring meshes

g.title: COMMENT_8fcff40+1
g.text: REAL_SEND_PKG8 carries obstruction mass loss information and is used even if RNODE=SNODE

g.title: COMMENT_902a240+1
g.text: Exchange of density and species mass fractions following the PREDICTOR update (CODE=1) or CORRECTOR (CODE=4) update

g.title: COMMENT_9068e80+1
g.text: Send pressure information at the end of the PREDICTOR (CODE=3) or CORRECTOR (CODE=6) stage of the time step

g.title: COMMENT_90f7e60+1
g.text: Get Number of PARTICLE Orphans (PARTICLEs that have left other meshes and are waiting to be picked up)

g.title: COMMENT_9136c20+1
g.text: Send mass losses from OBSTRUCTIONs that only border the current mesh

g.title: COMMENT_9162ea0+1
g.text: For each mesh, NM, controlled by the current MPI process, RNODE, loop over all
other meshes, NOM, and load data received into the appropriate arrays.

g.title: COMMENT_9169300+1
g.text: Unpack densities and species mass fractions in the PREDICTOR (CODE=1) and CORRECTOR (CODE=4) step

g.title: COMMENT_9188c20+1
g.text: Unpack densities and species mass fractions following PREDICTOR exchange

g.title: COMMENT_9164ac0+1
g.text: Unpack pressure following PREDICTOR stage of time step

g.title: COMMENT_91c4e00+1
g.text: Unpack radiation information at the end of the CORRECTOR stage of the time step

g.title: COMMENT_91cdc80+1
g.text: Unpack back wall information at the end of the CORRECTOR stage of the time step

g.title: COMMENT_91fe6e0+1
g.text: Unpack mass losses from OBST WALL cells in neighboring meshes

g.title: COMMENT_91fe6e0+2
g.text: CODE 16: MESH that contains the OBST unpacks M2%REAL_RECV_PKG8 which contains the mass lost by exterior cell faces.
CODE 17: MESH that contains the OBST packs up its new masses into REAL_SEND_PKG8
CODE 18: The MESHes containing the exterior cell faces receives the new mass of the OBST that lives in neighboring mesh.
